-- Whole-model verification summary
----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Fixed type error: target field in REQ_ATC_PRI_01 expects Resource, but predicates used Interface sigs as targets; added concrete Resource sigs (RunwaySlotResource, FlightScheduleResource, SafetyConstraintsResource) and updated all target references accordingly.
-- Summary 2: Added resource_ownership fact to satisfy owner_always_accessible invariant by setting owner and accessible for new resources.
-- Summary 3: Preserved all original comments, including incomplete annotated blocks.
-- Assumption 1: Resource ownership and accessibility are set to all actors (Actor set) for simplicity to avoid access control violations in the abstract model.
-- Assumption 2: The model abstracts away explicit flight and slot entities; states Pre1/Pre2, Post1/Post2 represent the allocation conditions indirectly.
-- Open issue 1: The model does not formally represent flights, slots, or the allocation process; acceptance criteria and test cases are verified only through state transitions and abstract constraints.
-- Open issue 2: Edge case ec_safe_1 uses 'no op.initiator.mayPerform & Read' as a proxy for 'no available slots', which may be too coarse.
-- Open issue 3: NFR facts (nfr_fact_performance_limit_channels, nfr_fact_availability_redundant_channels) together force exactly two channels per operation, which might conflict with some reachability predicates if they require a specific single channel.


